            <div class="prose max-w-none" x-show="lang === 'en'" x-cloak>
                <h2>Why Your Account Needs Regular Audits</h2>
<p>In overseas ad delivery, account bans are every operations team's nightmare. One ban can mean suspended campaigns, unusable balances, and time lost on re-verification—double losses: money and timing.</p>
<p>Compliance audits aren't about pleasing platforms—they're proactive risk management. This article breaks audits into actionable checklists with inspection frequency, making compliance work truly executable.</p>
<hr />
<h2>Daily Audits: 5 Minutes Daily, Check These 3 Things</h2>
<blockquote>
<p><strong>1. Account Status Confirmation</strong><br />
- Log into the ad dashboard, verify account displays normally (no red warnings, no permission issues)<br />
- Check if投放countries/regions match certified qualifications<br />
- Confirm campaign/ad group statuses are properly enabled</p>
<p><strong>2. Balance and Top-up Records</strong><br />
- Verify today's spend is within normal range (abnormal high spend often indicates creative or targeting issues)<br />
- Confirm top-up amounts match billing statements<br />
- If balance alerts are configured, verify alert notifications trigger properly</p>
<p><strong>3. Core Ad Performance Monitoring</strong><br />
- Watch for abnormal fluctuations in CTR and CVR<br />
- Check if ads were auto-paused due to low quality scores</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Frequency</strong>: Once daily, ideally before launching</p>
<hr />
<h2>Weekly Audits: Once Weekly, Systematic Investigation</h2>
<h3>Policy Compliance Checks</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Review latest policy announcements from Meta/Google/TikTok</li>
<li>[ ] Cross-check recent updates against existing ads for sensitive industry violations</li>
<li>[ ] Confirm landing page content matches ad promises without exaggeration</li>
</ul>
<h3>Creative Compliance Review</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Check Item</th>
<th>Standards</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Copy</td>
<td>No absolute terms ("best," "#1"), no false rankings</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Images</td>
<td>No other brand logos, no unauthorized celebrity images</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Claims</td>
<td>Special categories (finance, healthcare) have corresponding qualifications</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Landing Pages</td>
<td>URLs match ad promises, no unexpected redirects</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h3>Account Security Verification</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Check for unfamiliar login IPs or devices</li>
<li>[ ] Confirm BM permission assignments are compliant</li>
<li>[ ] Review if ad account is linked to accounts of unknown origin</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2>Monthly Audits: Deep Inspection Monthly, Prevention Over Cure</h2>
<h3>Financial Compliance Reconciliation</h3>
<blockquote>
<ul>
<li>Match monthly spend invoices against top-up expenses</li>
<li>Verify rebates/discounts properly credited</li>
<li>Investigate abnormal spend orders</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<h3>Account Health Assessment</h3>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Metric</th>
<th>Risk Threshold</th>
<th>Action</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Account violations</td>
<td>&gt;2 times in 1 month</td>
<td>Pause campaigns, investigate root cause</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Ad review rejection rate</td>
<td>&gt;30%</td>
<td>Full creative compliance review</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Low quality score ad ratio</td>
<td>&gt;50%</td>
<td>Optimize landing pages and creatives</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h2>High-Frequency Violation Checklist: Avoid These Traps</h2>
<ol>
<li><strong>Click baiting</strong>: Ad copy contains forced language like "Click to get," "Limited time offer"</li>
<li><strong>False scarcity</strong>: Claims "Only X left" but no actual stock limits</li>
<li><strong>Missing privacy policies</strong>: Pages collecting user data lack privacy agreement links</li>
<li><strong>Audience overlap</strong>: Multiple ad accounts running same product causing internal competition</li>
<li><strong>Abnormal payment methods</strong>: Frequent payment changes or using top-up channels of unknown origin</li>
</ol>
<hr />
<h2>Emergency Response Process</h2>
<p>When account violations appear, follow these steps:</p>
<p><strong>Step 1</strong>: Screenshot the violation notice, record violation time</p>
<p><strong>Step 2</strong>: Pause relevant ads or entire campaign (prevent further violations)</p>
<p><strong>Step 3</strong>: Review platform appeal portal, prepare appeal materials</p>
<p><strong>Step 4</strong>: Rectify based on violation type (modify creatives/adjust targeting/supply qualifications)</p>
<p><strong>Step 5</strong>: Submit appeal, wait for platform response (usually 1-3 business days)</p>
<hr />
<h2>Operations Checklist: Compliance Audit Execution Template</h2>
<h3>Daily Checks</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Account status normal</li>
<li>[ ] Balance sufficient, no abnormalities</li>
<li>[ ] Ads running properly</li>
</ul>
<h3>Weekly Checks</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Policy updates reviewed</li>
<li>[ ] Creative compliance verified</li>
<li>[ ] Account security confirmed</li>
</ul>
<h3>Monthly Checks</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Financial reconciliation completed</li>
<li>[ ] Account health assessment finished</li>
<li>[ ] Important data backed up</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h2>Final Thoughts</h2>
<p>Compliance audits aren't emergency repairs—they're part of daily operations. Integrate checks into workflows, use tools or spreadsheets to record results, and your team can run ads consistently and stably.</p>
<p>For multi-account managers, establish independent audit files per account. For new operations staff, print this checklist, verify each item, and after a month you'll feel the peace of mind that compliant delivery brings.</p>
